		Comment <a href="#c_1713681202">27</a> by Daniel Espeset
		posted on 11/25/2008 at 2:59 AM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>@Richard Steele / Ray Camden</p><p>I had the same problem: couldn't get the newsfeed pod to correctly display a .cfm feed.  The feed is completely valid and works in all feed readers.  The quick solution I used was to save the output of that .cfm file and write a .xml file just like Richard mentioned above.  The code I used is quite simple:</p><p>&lt;!--- save the output of our feed.cfm into a variable ---&gt;<br>&lt;cfsavecontent variable="myFeed"&gt;&lt;cfinclude template="feed.cfm"&gt;&lt;/cfsavecontent&gt;</p><p>&lt;!--- display it (optional) ---&gt;<br>&lt;cfoutput&gt;<br>#myFeed#<br>&lt;/cfoutput&gt;</p><p>&lt;!--- write the variable into a .xml file ---&gt;<br>&lt;cffile action="write"<br>        output="#myFeed#"<br>        file="#ExpandPath('path/feed.xml')#"&gt;</p><p>You can run this with a scheduler or attach it to the operation that adds items to your original feed.  Then configure the pod to read from the .xml file and it will work just fine.</p><p>(I realize this is months late and a clunky solution, but oh well)</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		